article.headline: New Orleans 55, Tulane 54
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Bo McCalebb hit the game-winning basket and added a big steal in the final 33 seconds as New Orleans defeated Tulane 55-54 Tuesday night. Down 54-53 after a Quincy Davis layup with 43 seconds left, McCalebb drove the lane to hit a high-arching, running jumper to put the Privateers up for good with 33 seconds left. On the ensuing possession, McCalebb knocked the ball off of Marcus Kinzer's leg out of bounds with nine seconds left to give New Orleans (3-3) the ball. After a quick foul that put McCalebb at the line, the sophomore Sun Belt preseason Player of the Year missed the front end of a 1-and-1 free throw opportunity. The Green Wave (1-3) got the ball to Kinzer who drove the right side of the lane but his shot was short as time expired. McCalebb led the Privateers with 18 points and Shawn Malloy added 10 rebounds and eight points. Kinzer led the Green Wave with 15 points.
